column5: I'm revamping my video site and turning them into youtube videos.. some of this stuff, I'm sure that newer members haven't seen before so as I do them , ill post them.  This one is a small laker, in about 15 feet of water, attacking a minnow head on a 12 inch piece of mono, behinf a dymara spoons used as a flasher.  This is one of the first underwater vids I did.
Pretty kewl TJ.  Thought I might better reply as no one else has and good God man, we don't want you to leave!
shhhh nobody say anything!! maybe he'll get the idea!
Nice... thanks .. Ill stick around.   This place is my only communication to the outside world...
Cool, get us some musky strikes on film
I got some of them as well....  ill see what I can do this morning.
I distinctly recall some other videos of pike takes!!  Seemed to be some unfortunate leader malfunctions..  Can ya dig those up too??
Very cool....can't wait to see more!!!
